   "source": [
    "üìñ Partial Derivatives Explained:\n",
    "For $f(x,y) = x^2 + y^2$:\n",
    "‚Ä¢ $‚àÇf/‚àÇx = 2x$ (derivative with respect to x, treating y as constant)\n",
    "‚Ä¢ $‚àÇf/‚àÇy = 2y$ (derivative with respect to y, treating x as constant)\n",
    "‚Ä¢ The gradient $‚àáf = (‚àÇf/‚àÇx, ‚àÇf/‚àÇy) = (2x, 2y)$\n",
    "‚Ä¢ Gradient points in direction of steepest increase\n",
    "‚Ä¢ For minimization, we go in the OPPOSITE direction: $-‚àáf$"
   ]
  },
